---
description: Use these rules whenever you create or edit API tests
alwaysApply: false
---

- You have API documentation in the `api-docs.json` file.
- Use Faker to generate random data for the tests.
- Use // given (test setup), // when (tested action), // then (test verification) comments to structure the tests.
- Do not add comments explaining the code
- Order tests by status code ascending (1xx, 2xx, 3xx, 4xx, 5xx)
- Do not create too many tests for input validation (http 400 bad request). Assume sufficient test coverage on unit test level.

